, authority, and the misuse of punishment in the preschool classroom. She shows a more effective and natural dynamic of limit-setting that emerges in the control children exert over their own fantasies. And here for the first time the author introduces a triumvirate of teachers (Paley herself and two apprentices) who reflect on the meaning of events unfolding before them.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 0aChild development. 0aEnfantsxDéveloppement. 0aFantasmes chez l'enfantxCas, Études de. 0aFantasy in childrenxCase studies. 0aPreschool teaching. 0aRelations maîtres-élèves. 0aTeacher-student relationships. 0aÉducation préscolaire. 7aEDUCATION / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Archive 1893-1999z978311044221240uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/9780674041868zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674041868423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780674041868/original  a978-3-11-044221-2  HUP eBook Package Archive 1893-1999c1893d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK